Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Collect & Deliver Get One
Arctic Trader - Collect & Deliver Get Several
Standard.Comment: Find other title or tweak the quest ("Don't know why they picked my freighter of all things!")

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Delivery Bring
Standard.Comment: Destroy his rep. Well, it's already destroyed. Maybe it's to get himself on their good side again. Advertisments, PR, sth. like that.

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Delivery Get
Standard.Comment: More specific; maybe the Custodians (or the Union, hint hint) don't give Ville enough supplies cause he lost the old ones or such things

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Tow Bring Home One
Standard.Comment: Did they stage the last attack? Means, that the player really helps the Orbital Watch guys? You can be more specific and declare them to be poachers or polluters. But Ville has a good heart.

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Destroy One
Standard.Comment: "Take it down" sounds like he really has no issues about using violence, but that's the point here. He could say something like: "I ... I'm not a friend of violence, but the Custodian Orders are clear" something like that. You don't have to say "There's a raider ship", that's already implied by the Quest Objectives. Try not to repeat info that's already in the objectives. Use the story text simply to provide context.

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Destroy Several
Standard.Comment: "Whole raider fleet" too military? Maybe, something like: There is illegal stuff going on here or they are preparing for an invasion.

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Track Several
Standard.Comment: But he does, giving the player the job. Try to hint more on the practical joke nature "They said this is so important and only someone as reliable as I could do it. But I need some help." Also: Avoid colleagues, it's more like fellows or fellow custodians

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Thieve & Deliver Get One
Arctic Trader - Thieve & Deliver Get Several
Standard.Comment: Avoid colleagues, it's more like fellows or fellow custodians

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Smuggle Bring
Standard.Comment: Be more casual: "No, I heard only good things about this trader." Find something else for 'renew her papers', more along the lines of 'doesn't provide info where the stuff came from', and then something like 'can happen to anybody'. Regarding the title, you can be more subtle here. There must be some slangy term for "unknowing smuggler"

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Goods Smuggle Bring
Standard.Comment: "pay out" to businesslike. For him it's about the food not the profits.

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Getaway Get One
Standard.Comment: Replace the "luck" part with, something like "I never imagined it would be this dangerous" or "I told him not to go"

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Getaway Bring Home One
Standard.Comment: You can be more casual here, also "poaching trap"... I know what you mean, but we need to get the point across in a different way ("They've taken the bait"), perhaps in the title.

Standard.Name: Arctic Trader - Assault Several
Standard.Comment: Find something else for the breakfast thing. Also, we have this theme in two other quests. Maybe ... how about renegade custodians and the rules dictate, well ...
